properties.Name: InsuranceCoverageType
properties.Description:
A coverage assigned to an insurance policy or product to cover special events or issues.

Ex:
LIABILITY
- Bodily injury
- First Aid Expenses
- Damage To Other Vehicles
- Court Costs
- Other Property Damage

MEDICAL EXPENSES
- Hospital Expenses
- Ambulance Fees
- Physician Services
- Funeral Expenses

COMPREHENSIVE
- Theft
- Fire
- Vandalism
- Collision with Animals
- Falling Objects
- Glass Breakage
- Flood
- Hail
- Windstorm

COLLISION
- Other Vehicles
- Stationary Objects
- Upset
- While Parked

UNINSURED MOTORIST
- Riding in your vehicle
- Property Damage

OTHER 
- Newly Acquired Vehicle
- Emergency Road Service
- Auto Rental Reimbursement
- Accidental Death and Dismemberment
- Combined Single Limit
- Drive-Other-Car (Endorsement)
- Extended Non-Lower Liability
***
- All Risk
- Labor Strike
- Perishing of Goods
- Pilferage
- Acts of God
- Acts of War
- Latent Defects In the Hull/Machinery
- Criminal Acts
- Negligence by Master/Crew
- Unseaworthiness of Vessel
